('5930', '490', 'description', '<h3>Description</h3>\r\nBall valves are mainly used when fast operation is required in the oil & gas, petrochemical, nuclear and power plants.\r\nThey are installed in the pipelines, in the power generation plants, in the water treatment and cryogenic applications.\r\n\r\n<h3>Design</h3>\r\naccording to API 6D, ASME B16.34\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Floating and Trunnion-mounted design</li>\r\n<li>Side entry and Top entry construction</li>\r\n<li>Full and Reduced bore</li>\r\n<li>Metal to metal and Soft seal seated</li>\r\n<li>Anti blow out stem</li>\r\n<li>Double block and bleed\r\n<li>Single or Double piston effect seats</li>\r\n<li>Sub-sea and Criogenic executions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFire safe tested API 6fa, API 607, ISO 10497\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Range of production</h3>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n	<div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n		<img src=\"http://sitindustrievalvometal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ball-valves_tabella1.png\" width=\"250px;\">\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n<strong>TRUNNION</strong>\r\n<table style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ENDS</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"6\">R.F. - R.T.J. - B.W.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>CLASS</td>\r\n<td>150</td>\r\n<td>300</td>\r\n<td>600</td>\r\n<td>900</td>\r\n<td>1500</td>\r\n<td>2500</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>NPS (up | to)</td>\r\n<td>60\"</td>\r\n<td>60\"</td>\r\n<td>60\"</td>\r\n<td>48\"</td>\r\n<td>36\"</td>\r\n<td>30\"</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n	<div class=\"col-lg-4\">\r\n		<img src=\"http://sitindustrievalvometal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ball-valves_tabella2.png\" width=\"250px;\">\r\n	</div>\r\n	<div class=\"col-lg-8\">\r\n<strong>FLOATING</strong>\r\n<table style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ENDS</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"6\">R.F. - R.T.J. - B.W. - S.W. - NPT</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>CLASS</td>\r\n<td>150</td>\r\n<td>300</td>\r\n<td>600</td>\r\n<td>900</td>\r\n<td>1500</td>\r\n<td>2500</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>NPS (up | to)</td>\r\n<td>6\"</td>\r\n<td>4\"</td>\r\n<td>3\"</td>\r\n<td>2\"</td>\r\n<td>2\"</td>\r\n<td>1\"1/4</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<small>All sizes and ratings available on demand.\r\nWe can supply ball valves with manual levers, gear operators, electric, pneumatic or hydraulic actuators.</small>\r\n\r\n<h3>Construction Materials</h3>\r\nValvometal can manufacture valves with all types of material complying with ASTM & ASME standards and in accordance to customer needs and specifications (NACE standard included). The main casted and forged materials used are:\r\n\r\n<p><strong>BODY</strong>\r\nForged carbon steel, stainless steel, special and exotic alloys. all casted steel materials for âtop entryâ type.</p>\r\n<p><strong>TRIM</strong>\r\nForged or pressed carbon steel, stainless steel, special and exotic alloys.</p>'),
